Chilean <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../950/61950.xml">
salad</link> is a salad containing <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../234/9940234.xml">
tomato</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../258/51258.xml">
onion</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../640/341640.xml">
coriander</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>, and sometimes with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../225/74225.xml">
chilli peppers</link>.  <p>

The onion may be soaked in boiling salted water, to soften it and reduce its sharpness.  It may also be soaked in cold water for an hour or so, or marinated with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../762/32762.xml">
vinegar</link>.</p>


